ActCanada Transportation Act
SubjectRegulations Amending the Railway Interswitching Regulations
PrecisRegulations Amending the RAILWAY INTERSWITCHING REGULATIONS in order to protect and advance the public interest in the economic well-being of Canadians and promote a fair and competitive market economy, specifically by increasing competition among railway companies and giving shippers access to alternative rail services, which will contribute to the ability of shippers of grain and other commodities to have improved access to domestic and export markets.
